    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-08T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="750"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A Combat Areas/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-08T18:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 8, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 8—5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2695. The Embassy is daily receiving numerous pressing inquiries from Americans
                    relative to the application of the neutrality laws to their residence in France
                    and travel through this country to other countries within the war zone as well
                    as to the United States upon vessels of belligerent nations. Instructions are
                    urgently requested<note n="68" xml:id="d750fn68">Notation on the file copy
                        indicates that circular telegram of November 17, 6 p.m., <ref
                            target="#pg_706">p. 706</ref>, and telegram No. 121, November 22, 6
                        p.m., <ref target="#pg_709">p. 709</ref>, were considered to have answered
                        this telegram.</note> in this regard and concerning the renewal of passports
                    beyond December 31 of those persons regularly residing here for business or
                    other reasons who are required to renew their French cards of identity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
